00:52:41.840 --> 00:52:44.320
attractive as his wife,
he's got a lot of

00:52:44.320 --> 00:52:45.660
money, celebrity status.

00:52:45.660 --> 00:52:46.760
And so there's good matching.

00:52:46.760 --> 00:52:52.070
And so the idea is that this
matching occurs in the market.

00:52:52.070 --> 00:52:55.730
Whether or not people like it
or they want it, it's the

00:52:55.730 --> 00:52:59.080
result of the market, the fact
that individuals differ in

00:52:59.080 --> 00:53:02.170
these endowments, that there is
competition for people with

00:53:02.170 --> 00:53:04.930
high endowments, and that there
is the laws of supply

00:53:04.930 --> 00:53:05.740
and demand.

00:53:05.740 --> 00:53:08.850
So good matching is a
good thing for you.

00:53:08.850 --> 00:53:10.120
It makes couple more stable.

00:53:10.120 --> 00:53:12.470
It makes it unlikely that the
relationship is associated

00:53:12.470 --> 00:53:15.670
with different cost/benefit
ratios for the two partners,

00:53:15.670 --> 00:53:18.900
and that might lead to one
partner to cheat or end the

00:53:18.900 --> 00:53:19.770
relationship.

00:53:19.770 --> 00:53:22.260
So how do you know where you
stand in the mating market,

00:53:22.260 --> 00:53:23.660
what's your mate value is.

00:53:23.660 --> 00:53:26.830
People pretty much figure out
the value of their endowments

00:53:26.830 --> 00:53:29.410
with experience, with feedback
from other people,

00:53:29.410 --> 00:53:31.980
particularly during adolescence,
and usually end

00:53:31.980 --> 00:53:36.470
up pairing with an individual
who has similar value.

00:53:36.470 --> 00:53:40.240
A human mating market is by no
means unique to our species.

00:53:40.240 --> 00:53:43.010
There's mating markets
like this in birds,

00:53:43.010 --> 00:53:44.690
other mammals, primates.

00:53:44.690 --> 00:53:46.350
And they're not all about sex.

00:53:46.350 --> 00:53:49.680
There are markets about other
things-- for example, in fish,

00:53:49.680 --> 00:53:54.490
there is a species of large fish
that needs smaller fish

00:53:54.490 --> 00:53:56.910
to swim inside their mouth and
clean their mouths from

00:53:56.910 --> 00:53:58.025
parasites and other things.

00:53:58.025 --> 00:54:00.860
These are called the cleaner
and the client.

00:54:00.860 --> 00:54:04.590
So studies have shown that how
each fish chooses a partner

00:54:04.590 --> 00:54:07.580
for this thing, it's a complex
operation that essentially

00:54:07.580 --> 00:54:08.450
involves a market.

00:54:08.450 --> 00:54:10.850
There are some cleaners, they
have very high endowments.

00:54:10.850 --> 00:54:11.705
They have a good reputation.

00:54:11.705 --> 00:54:12.790
They do a good job.

00:54:12.790 --> 00:54:13.810
They don't cheat.

00:54:13.810 --> 00:54:16.680
There are [INAUDIBLE]

00:54:16.680 --> 00:54:19.452
